race.comment: TAMPA BAY (8) thirteen-start maiden who finds a winnable race. Attacked the line late when back in class for a tidy fourth over 1000m at Scone. Drops further in weight with Stanley's claim and adept in all going. MISS MOLLY ROCKET (3) returned a good set of closing splits on debut when savaging the line late to finish fourth over 1000m at Port Macquarie. Trained on the track and no shock to see her go on with it now. LOVE YOU ANYWAY (5) improved showing two-back when placing over 900m at Newcastle from back in the field. Had excuses from the wide gate when fourth over 900m at Newcastle. Hard fit now on the backup. Each way. PRIZE WRITER (1) Written By mare from Finest Choice on debut for the Archibald yard. Fitted with the five trials and she has a host of gear changes on for this. Must respect from the inside draw.
